        "ai_gen_block_4b89c2e_Bjc4nx": {
          "type": "ai_gen_block_4b89c2e",
          "settings": {
            "text_content": "<p><strong>Our Story<br/><br/></strong>Since 1952, Janardhana Silk House has carried forward a living tradition—one that begins not in a showroom, but in the rhythmic poetry of the loom. Every creation is born from the patient dialogue between skilled hands, pure silk threads, and time-honored techniques passed down through generations of master weavers across India.</p><p></p><p>The journey starts with the finest silk yarns, carefully selected for their strength, sheen, and softness. These threads are dyed in rich, enduring hues—each color chosen to echo celebration, heritage, and grace. On traditional looms, artisans interlace warp and weft with remarkable precision, transforming delicate strands into enduring works of art. Intricate motifs emerge slowly—temple borders, floral vines, and timeless patterns—each detail woven with devotion rather than haste.</p><p>What makes the craft extraordinary is not just technique, but intention. Every saree carries the wisdom of decades: the understanding of balance, drape, texture, and elegance. It is this harmony of heritage and craftsmanship that gives each piece its soul.</p><p></p><p>From the quiet artistry of the weaving centers to the hands of those who wear them, Janardhana Silk House serves as a bridge between tradition and today. By preserving authentic weaving practices while making them accessible to modern patrons, the house ensures that India’s textile legacy continues to be lived, worn, and celebrated.</p><p>More than fabric, each weave is a story of time, care, and cultural pride—brought lovingly from loom to life.</p>",
            "font_family": "assistant_n4",
            "font_size": 16,
            "line_height": 1.5,
            "text_alignment": "left",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "background_color": "#ffffff",
            "link_color": "#000000",
            "link_hover_color": "#666666",
            "desktop_width_percent": 100,
            "padding_top": 20,
            "padding_bottom": 20,
